 :@-party: /at'par`tee/ [from the @-sign in an Internet address] n. (alt.
`@-sign party' /at'si:n par`tee/) A semi-closed party thrown for hackers at a
science-fiction convention (esp. the annual Worldcon); one must have a
{network address} to get in, or at least be in company with someone who does.
One of the most reliable opportunities for hackers to meet face to face with
people who might otherwise be represented by mere phosphor dots on their
screens. Compare {boink}.